data.text:
PRIOR TO PENN STATE

Attended Wissahickon high school...Ranked by Inside Lacrosse as the No. 7 overall recruit & No. 4 attackman. Ranked by NLF Rankings as the No. 5 overall recruit & No. 3 attackman. Selected to the New Balance Senior All-America Game and the Nike Senior All-America Game. Named a USA Lacrosse All-American and USA Lacrosse All-Academic for junior & senior seasons.. Holds school record for goals in a season (65) during both sophomore & senior seasons. Named to the Suburban One League - first team attack for sophomore, junior & senior seasons.... Named team captain & team MVP his senior season... Played club lacrosse for the Philadelphia Freedom.

PERSONAL

Parents are Steve & Tiffany Lehman. Has two siblings, Brett and Carly Lehman. Father, Steve, played lacrosse at Penn State... Brother, Brett, runs track at Providence College.... Uncle, Chris Alston, played football at Penn State... Aunt Tricia (Lehman) Alston, played tennis at Penn State.......Currently undecided on major.
